{"word":"πιαίνω","slug":"πιαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πιαίνω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πίων'><el>πίων</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make fat, fatten</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>π. χθόνα</el> <i>to fatten</i> the soil, of a dead man, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be</i> or <i>become fat</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to increase, enlarge</i>, <el>πλοῦτον</el> <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to make wanton, excite</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to wax fat and wanton</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>ἔχθεσιν πιαίνεσθαι</el> <i>to batten on</i> quarrels, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}